The paper discusses the use of traditional AI reasoning techniques in coordinating teams of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in dynamic environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on developing an agent architecture and reasoning algorithms for coordinating UAVs, which falls under the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The use of UAVs also suggests that the paper may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also addresses the challenge of coordinating UAVs in network-centric environments, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) in developing the agent architecture, which suggests that the paper may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
